09/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- About 64% of Serbian citizens say former Bosnian Serb military commander Ratko Mladic should not be arrested and transferred to The Hague war crimes tribunal, according to a survey commissioned by the OSCE mission in Serbia and the Belgrade Centre for Human Rights. 
According to results published on Tuesday (December 8th), 25% of those questioned support Mladic's arrest while 11% have no position on the issue. 
About 56% say Mladic is responsible for war crimes, while 31% are not aware of the charges. 
The survey was conducted several months ago. 
(Politika, Tanjug, Beta - 08/12/09)
